@baseUrl = http://localhost:5129
@token = YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### Login to get token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/Auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{"email": "admin@etr.com", "password": "123456"}

### ----------------------------------------------------
### ================= MODULE: Accounts =================
### [Module/Flow]: Identity & Access Management
[Core Responsibility]: Retrieves all accounts.
[Target Audience]: Admin
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/Accounts
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### [Module/Flow]: Identity & Access Management
[Core Responsibility]: Creates a new system account.
[Target Audience]: Admin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/Accounts
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "string",
  "password": "string",
  "roleId": 1,
  "departmentId": 1
}

### [Module/Flow]: Identity & Access Management
[Core Responsibility]: Retrieves a specific account by ID.
[Target Audience]: Admin
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/Accounts/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### [Module/Flow]: Identity & Access Management
[Core Responsibility]: Deletes an account from the system.
[Target Audience]: Admin
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/Accounts/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### [Module/Flow]: Identity & Access Management
[Core Responsibility]: Updates the status of an existing account.
[Target Audience]: Admin
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/Accounts/1/status
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "string"
}

